 agents. The result is a vibrant and up-to-date picture of politics in Japan today that also addresses masculine gender expectations in a male-dominated political world, the connection between gendered identity and ethical being, and the process by which men who are neither dominant nor marginal to their communities assert themselves both with and against power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMasculinityxPolitical aspectszJapan. 0aMenxPolitical activityzJapan. 0aPolitical culturezJapan. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  abreadwinners.  acampaign functions.  acheating.  acitizens referendum movement.  ademocracy.  ademocratic practice.  aethical agents.  aethical being.  aethics.  aethnography.  agender expectations.  agender studies.  agendered identity.  agood man.  ainheritor.  ajapan.  ajapanese masculinity.  ajapanese men.  ajapanese politics.  aleadership.  amale dominated political world.  amasculine honor.  amasculinity.  amorality.  apolitical choices.  apolitics.  apower.  arural leaders.  astrategy sessions.  atokyo ward assembly.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025916440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094505040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945050/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY